10 grahm crackers
1 tsp ground cinnamon
5 tbsp melted unsalted butter

Grind the crackers and add with the liquids. Press down in cake pan and bake for 12 minutes in 350 oven. 

5 oz. bittersweet chocolate
1 tbsp. of espresso (grinds)

On mild double boiler, add chopped chocolate and coffee. 

1 cup sugar
1/4 cup corn starch
1 + 1/4 cup cream cheese
1 tsp vanilla
1 tsp almond extract
3 eggs
1/2 cup sour cream

Combine slowly with with chocolate. In 350 degree oven, let cook for one hour, then turn off heat, open door, and let rest in oven for 1 and a half more hours. Let cool before serving.
